# Deploy lanes — minimum validation

After any change, pick the **minimum** lane that can exercise it. Prefer FE-only or local `uv run` / pytest. Image publish and SAM deploy are expensive; only trigger when the change cannot be validated without them.

## Lanes

| Lane | Paths | Validate with | Do not |
|---|---|---|---|
| **FE only** | `web/**` (and copy/docs) | `npm run dev` / `npm run build` against existing stack `ApiUrl` / `WebSocketUrl` | Any AWS deploy; do not wait on Python/ARM64/package CI |
| **Control plane (SAM)** | `src/dungeon_agent/control_plane/**`, `src/dungeon_agent/data_plane/**`, `src/dungeon_agent/plane_shared/**`, `infra/control-plane/**` | Push to `main` (path-filtered) or `workflow_dispatch` on `.github/workflows/deploy-control-plane.yml`; Python CI only | Rebuild MicroVM image; skip ARM64/package CI |
| **MicroVM image** | `Dockerfile`, `scripts/build_microvm_image*`, game/API runtime under `src/dungeon_agent/**` **outside** `control_plane/` / `data_plane/` / `plane_shared/` (also `pyproject.toml` / `uv.lock` when they affect the image) | Tag `v*` / `release.yml`, or `python -m scripts.build_microvm_image`; then resolve new `IMAGE_VERSION`; full Python + ARM64 + package CI | SAM-deploy unless CP env/contract also changed |

## CI (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`)

Path filters mirror the lanes. Jobs are conditional; the aggregating job named **CI** always runs so merges are not blocked by skipped lane jobs.

- `web/**` → Frontend build only
- `control_plane/**` / `data_plane/**` / `plane_shared/**` (and other Python paths) → Python 3.14; no container/package unless MicroVM paths also changed
- MicroVM paths (guest `api/`, Dockerfile, image builder — not the SAM plane packages) → Python + ARM64 + package
- Docs/meta only → Detect lanes + CI gate (green)

Prefer requiring the **CI** check in branch protection, not the individual lane job names.

## Compose when needed

- CP API/WS contract + web client → SAM deploy **and** FE refresh
- Game rules inside MicroVM + turn worker env/contract → image publish **and** SAM deploy
- FE polish only → never wait on image or SAM

## Agent behavior

- After a `web/`-only change: suggest `npm run dev`; do **not** propose SAM or image publish.
- After turn-worker / SAM template / CP Lambda changes: propose CP deploy only.
- After game-runtime changes that ship in the MicroVM: propose image publish and mention picking up the new `IMAGE_VERSION`.
